<small>Aramaic form: **<big>[[H7792|שׁוּר]]</big>**</small>
 II. <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּר‎</span> **noun [masculine]** ==wall== (Aramaic <span class="bdbLangAramaic">‎שׁוּרָא‎</span>, <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,">); — [[Gen.49.22|Gen 49:22]] (poem in [[BDB#J|J]]), [[2Sam.22.30|2Sam 22:30]] = [[Ps.18.30|Ps 18:30]] plural suffix <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּרֹתָם‎</span> [[Job.24.11|Job 24:11]] ***their walls*** [[BDB#De|De]] [[BDB#Di|Di]] [[BDB#De|De]], compare [[BDB#Bu|Bu]]; but see  <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּרָה‎</span> infra; <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שָׁרוֺתֶיהָ‎</span> [[Jer.5.10|Jer 5:10]] = ***its walls***, according to [[BDB#Vrss|Vrss]] [[BDB#AV|AV]] [[BDB#RV|RV]] [[BDB#Gf|Gf]] [[BDB#Gie|Gie]], read then <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎׳‎</span><span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שֻׁ‎</span>, but see id. 

 [<span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּרָה‎</span>] **noun feminine** probably ==row of olives or vines== (so [[BDB#Du|Du]] [[BDB#Buhl|Buhl]] and others; compare Late Hebrew <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּרָה‎</span>, Jewish-Aramaic <span class="bdbLangAramaic">‎שׁוּרְתָא‎</span> ***row***, whence modern Arabic <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> as loan-word, compare [[BDB#Vogelst|Vogelst]]<sup>Land wirthschaft 41 f.</sup>); — plural suffix <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּרֹתְם‎</span> [[Job.24.11|Job 24:11]] (al. II. <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּר‎</span>); [[BDB#Bu|Bu]] and [[BDB#Du|Du]] strike out suffix; here also [[Jer.5.10|Jer 5:10]] (reading <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎׳‎</span><span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שֻׁ‎</span>) [[BDB#Du|Du]] [[BDB#Buhl|Buhl]] [[BDB#Dr|Dr]], ***her*** (vine-)***rows***, but see II.  <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שׁוּר‎</span>. <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שַׁוְשָׁא‎</span> **proper name, masculine** [[1Chr.18.16|1Chr 18:16]], see <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שְׂרָיָה‎</span>.
